GAP 1: Default event matches Progress in Rust but NOT in Go
================================================================================

**Severity**: Bug - causes incorrect webhook firing behavior

**Go Code** (middleware/job/webhook.go lines 27-31):
```go
if et == StateChange && wh.Event != webhook.EventJobStateChange && wh.Event != webhook.EventDefault {
    continue
}
if et == Progress && wh.Event != webhook.EventJobProgress {
    continue
}
// Go: default event (empty string) does NOT match Progress
```

**Rust Code** (middleware/job/webhook.rs lines 98-105):
```rust
match et {
    EventType::StateChange => {
        event.is_empty() || event == EVENT_JOB_STATE_CHANGE || event == EVENT_DEFAULT
    }
    EventType::Progress => event.is_empty() || event == EVENT_JOB_PROGRESS,
    // ^ BUG: Rust treats empty/default event as matching Progress
    _ => false,
}
```

**Expected Fix**:
When et == Progress, the condition should NOT fire for default/empty event:
```rust
EventType::Progress => event == EVENT_JOB_PROGRESS,  // Remove event.is_empty()
```

